{"author":{"id":"cc8322a500b8739c77faac347808f6026d9ccb7880d0aaa7ad76754163cd7fdb"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1782568927,"nonce":"ERHn1wK2gBp1/mfzorZO2oP7XMs=","kind":"plan","title":"Slice 5 — Hygiene \u0026 consolidation Implementation Plan"},{"type":3,"timestamp":1782568927,"nonce":"iyW4uyYTgHs1q5fWrSbgE91MJUU=","body":"# Slice 5 — Hygiene \u0026 consolidation Implementation Plan\n\n\u003e **For agentic workers:** REQUIRED SUB-SKILL: Use superpowers:subagent-driven-development (recommended) or superpowers:executing-plans to implement this plan task-by-task. Steps use checkbox (`- [ ]`) syntax for tracking.\n\n**Goal:** Make kref stay legible as it grows — `list` self-cleans (hides superseded, collapses duplicate titles), `kref tidy` surfaces consolidation candidates, and `kref links`/`kref tree`/`kref supersede` expose and act on the existing link facet.\n\n**Architecture:** No new op types — the `links` facet already exists (`AddLink`/`RemoveLink`, iota 5–6). Everything new is a thin store query over compiled snapshots or a human-render affordance; the only new persistence is a `Store.AddLink` wrapper (mirrors `Store.AddLabel`). Query-result types live in the **entry** package (like the existing `entry.LogEntry`/`entry.BodyVersion`) so the **render** package stays pure (entry + stdlib only, no `store` import); cross-entry scanning logic lives in **store**; the CLI stays a thin adapter routing through `emit`. Clean-by-default is a human-render concern only, so `list --json` is byte-for-byte unchanged.\n\n**Tech Stack:** Go, cobra (CLI), git-bug entity/dag (storage), ginkgo/gomega (tests), Taskfile (`task test`/`task lint`). Reference spec: `docs/dev/specs/2026-06-20-unified-entry-model-design.md` §4.4 (build decisions) and §11 (resolved hygiene questions).\n\n---\n\n## Conventions for every task\n\n- **TDD loop per task:** write the failing test → run it, confirm it fails → implement the minimal real code → run it, confirm it passes → `gofmt -w` the touched files → commit.\n- **Test runner:** all commands assume `GOTOOLCHAIN=auto` (system Go is 1.26.3; `go.mod` wants 1.26.4). The `cmd/kref` suite additionally needs `KREF_GITLEAKS=$(pwd)/bin/gitleaks` (its ingest tests shell out to gitleaks). The Taskfile sets both — `task test` and `task lint` are the canonical runners. For targeted runs:\n  - entry/store/render: `GOTOOLCHAIN=auto go test ./internal/entry/... ./internal/store/... ./internal/render/...`\n  - cmd/kref: `KREF_GITLEAKS=$(pwd)/bin/gitleaks GOTOOLCHAIN=auto go test ./cmd/kref/...`\n- **Commit hygiene:** stage files by name (never `git add -A`). Every commit message ends with the trailer:\n  `Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) \u003cnoreply@anthropic.com\u003e`\n- **JSON:** additive only — new types, snake_case `json:` tags; existing keys frozen.\n- **The op-iota append-only rule does not apply this slice** (no new op types are added).\n\n## File structure\n\n| File | Change | Responsibility |\n|------|--------|----------------|\n| `internal/entry/operations.go` | modify | add `NormalizeTitle` beside `DeriveTitle`/`FirstHeading` |\n| `internal/entry/hygiene.go` | create | slice-5 query-result types: `LinkRef`, `LinkView`, `TreeNode`, `TidyEntry`, `DuplicateGroup`, `TidyReport` |\n| `internal/store/hygiene.go` | create | `AddLink`, `Supersede`, `Links`, `Tree`, `Tidy` |\n| `internal/render/render.go` | modify | `List` gains a `showAll` param + duplicate-collapse/superseded-hide |\n| `internal/render/hygiene.go` | create | `Links`, `Tree`, `Tidy` renderers |\n| `cmd/kref/commands.go` | modify | `newListCmd` (+`--all`), `newSupersedeCmd`, `newLinksCmd`, `newTreeCmd`, `newTidyCmd` |\n| `cmd/kref/main.go` | modify | register the four new commands |\n| `internal/entry/normalize_test.go` | create | `NormalizeTitle` unit tests |\n| `internal/store/hygiene_test.go` | create | store-method tests |\n| `internal/render/render_test.go` | modify | update existing `render.List` calls to the new arity |\n| `internal/render/hygiene_test.go` | create | renderer tests |\n| `cmd/kref/cli_test.go` | modify | black-box CLI tests for the new behaviour |\n| `README.md`, `CHANGELOG.md` | modify | user docs |\n\n---\n\n## Task 1: `entry.NormalizeTitle`\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `internal/entry/normalize_test.go`\n- Modify: `internal/entry/operations.go` (add function after `DeriveTitle`, ~line 319)\n\n- [ ] **Step 1: Write the failing test**\n\nCreate `internal/entry/normalize_test.go`. NOTE: use the EXTERNAL test package `entry_test` and qualify calls as `entry.NormalizeTitle` — the `entry` package has a top-level `type Entry struct`, which collides with ginkgo's dot-imported `Entry` (DescribeTable DSL) if you use `package entry`. Every existing entry test uses `entry_test` for this reason.\n\n```go\npackage entry_test\n\nimport (\n\t. \"github.com/onsi/ginkgo/v2\"\n\t. \"github.com/onsi/gomega\"\n\n\t\"github.com/riotbox/kref/internal/entry\"\n)\n\nvar _ = Describe(\"NormalizeTitle\", func() {\n\tIt(\"lowercases, trims, and collapses internal whitespace\", func() {\n\t\tExpect(entry.NormalizeTitle(\"  Auth   Design  \")).To(Equal(\"auth design\"))\n\t})\n\tIt(\"collapses tabs and newlines to single spaces\", func() {\n\t\tExpect(entry.NormalizeTitle(\"Auth\\tDesign\\nflow\")).To(Equal(\"auth design flow\"))\n\t})\n\tIt(\"keeps punctuation significant\", func() {\n\t\tExpect(entry.NormalizeTitle(\"Auth: Design\")).To(Equal(\"auth: design\"))\n\t})\n\tIt(\"maps whitespace-only to empty\", func() {\n\t\tExpect(entry.NormalizeTitle(\"   \")).To(Equal(\"\"))\n\t})\n})\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 2: Run test to verify it fails**\n\nRun: `GOTOOLCHAIN=auto go test ./internal/entry/...`\nExpected: FAIL — compile error `undefined: NormalizeTitle`.\n\n- [ ] **Step 3: Write minimal implementation**\n\nIn `internal/entry/operations.go`, add after `DeriveTitle` (after ~line 319, before `operationUnmarshaler`):\n\n```go\n// NormalizeTitle folds a title into its duplicate-grouping key: lowercased,\n// surrounding whitespace trimmed, internal whitespace runs collapsed to a single\n// space. Punctuation is significant. This is deliberately codepoint-simple (no\n// Unicode NFC folding) so it needs nothing beyond the standard library;\n// canonical/fuzzy matching is the deferred search-index tier.\nfunc NormalizeTitle(s string) string {\n\treturn strings.ToLower(strings.Join(strings.Fields(s), \" \"))\n}\n```\n\n(`strings` is already imported in `operations.go`.)\n\n- [ ] **Step 4: Run test to verify it passes**\n\nRun: `GOTOOLCHAIN=auto go test ./internal/entry/...`\nExpected: PASS.\n\n- [ ] **Step 5: gofmt + commit**\n\n```bash\ngofmt -w internal/entry/operations.go internal/entry/normalize_test.go\ngit add internal/entry/operations.go internal/entry/normalize_test.go\ngit commit -m \"feat(entry): NormalizeTitle for duplicate-title grouping\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## Task 2: clean-by-default `list` (hide superseded, collapse duplicates, `--all`)\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `internal/render/render.go` (`List`, ~lines 106–168)\n- Modify: `internal/render/render_test.go` (existing `render.List` call sites)\n- Create: (new tests appended to) `internal/render/render_test.go`\n- Modify: `cmd/kref/commands.go` (`newListCmd`, ~lines 293–337)\n- Modify: `cmd/kref/cli_test.go` (append tests)\n\n- [ ] **Step 1: Update existing render tests to the new arity**\n\nThe `List` signature gains a trailing `showAll bool`. Pass `true` at every existing call site to preserve today's behaviour (no hiding, no collapse). There are nine calls in `internal/render/render_test.go` (lines 57, 65, 78, 84, 90, 91, 119, 205, 213). For each, append `, true` before the closing `)`. Example:\n\n```go\n// before\nrender.List(\u0026b, []*entry.Snapshot{snap(\"shared\", \"spec\", \"open\", \"Auth\", false)}, false)\n// after\nrender.List(\u0026b, []*entry.Snapshot{snap(\"shared\", \"spec\", \"open\", \"Auth\", false)}, false, true)\n```\n\nVerify none remain at the old arity:\n\n```bash\ngrep -n \"render.List(\" internal/render/render_test.go\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 2: Write the failing tests (new collapse/hide behaviour)**\n\nAppend to `internal/render/render_test.go` (inside the top-level `Describe`, or as a new `Describe` in the same file). These use the existing `snap` helper; confirm its signature first with `grep -n \"func snap(\" internal/render/render_test.go` — it is `snap(tier, kind, status, title string, deleted bool) *entry.Snapshot`. Build snapshots directly where you need to control `UpdatedAt`:\n\n```go\nvar _ = Describe(\"List clean view\", func() {\n\tIt(\"collapses duplicate normalized titles into one (×N) row when showAll is false\", func() {\n\t\tvar b bytes.Buffer\n\t\titems := []*entry.Snapshot{\n\t\t\t{ID: \"aaa1\", Tier: \"shared\", Kind: \"note\", Status: \"open\", Title: \"Auth Design\"},\n\t\t\t{ID: \"bbb2\", Tier: \"shared\", Kind: \"note\", Status: \"open\", Title: \"auth   design\"},\n\t\t}\n\t\trender.List(\u0026b, items, false, false)\n\t\tout := b.String()\n\t\tExpect(out).To(ContainSubstring(\"(×2)\"))\n\t\tExpect(out).To(ContainSubstring(\"1 entry\"))\n\t})\n\tIt(\"hides superseded entries when showAll is false but shows them when true\", func() {\n\t\titems := []*entry.Snapshot{\n\t\t\t{ID: \"aaa1\", Tier: \"shared\", Kind: \"note\", Status: \"superseded\", Title: \"Gone\"},\n\t\t\t{ID: \"bbb2\", Tier: \"shared\", Kind: \"note\", Status: \"open\", Title: \"Here\"},\n\t\t}\n\t\tvar clean bytes.Buffer\n\t\trender.List(\u0026clean, items, false, false)\n\t\tExpect(clean.String()).NotTo(ContainSubstring(\"Gone\"))\n\t\tExpect(clean.String()).To(ContainSubstring(\"Here\"))\n\n\t\tvar all bytes.Buffer\n\t\trender.List(\u0026all, items, false, true)\n\t\tExpect(all.String()).To(ContainSubstring(\"Gone\"))\n\t})\n})\n```\n\nConfirm `bytes` and `entry` are imported in the test file (they are used by existing tests; if a new `Describe` block needs them they are already in the file's import set).\n\n- [ ] **Step 3: Run tests to verify they fail**\n\nRun: `GOTOOLCHAIN=auto go test ./internal/render/...`\nExpected: FAIL — `List` does not accept four arguments / collapse output absent.\n\n- [ ] **Step 4: Implement `List` with the new behaviour**\n\nReplace the `List` function in `internal/render/render.go` (the block at ~lines 106–168) with:\n\n```go\ntype listRow struct {\n\tsnap  *entry.Snapshot\n\tcount int\n}\n\n// List renders entries as a headered, tier-sorted table with a count footer.\n// Ordering is deterministic: tier rank → kind → title → id. Unless showAll is\n// set, superseded entries are hidden and entries sharing a normalized title\n// collapse into a single \"(×N)\" row (representative = most recently updated,\n// tie-broken by id).\nfunc List(w io.Writer, items []*entry.Snapshot, color, showAll bool) {\n\trows := listRows(items, showAll)\n\tif len(rows) == 0 {\n\t\tfmt.Fprintln(w, \"no entries\")\n\t\treturn\n\t}\n\tsort.SliceStable(rows, func(i, j int) bool {\n\t\ta, b := rows[i].snap, rows[j].snap\n\t\tif ra, rb := tierRank(a.Tier), tierRank(b.Tier); ra != rb {\n\t\t\treturn ra \u003c rb\n\t\t}\n\t\tif a.Kind != b.Kind {\n\t\t\treturn a.Kind \u003c b.Kind\n\t\t}\n\t\tif a.Title != b.Title {\n\t\t\treturn a.Title \u003c b.Title\n\t\t}\n\t\treturn a.ID.String() \u003c b.ID.String()\n\t})\n\n\ttierW, kindW, statusW := len(\"TIER\"), len(\"KIND\"), len(\"STATUS\")\n\tfor _, r := range rows {\n\t\tit := r.snap\n\t\tif n := utf8.RuneCountInString(tierPlain(it.Tier)); n \u003e tierW {\n\t\t\ttierW = n\n\t\t}\n\t\tif n := utf8.RuneCountInString(it.Kind); n \u003e kindW {\n\t\t\tkindW = n\n\t\t}\n\t\tif n := utf8.RuneCountInString(it.Status); n \u003e statusW {\n\t\t\tstatusW = n\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\tconst idW = 12\n\n\tfmt.Fprintf(w, \"%s  %s  %s  %s  %s\\n\",\n\t\tpad(\"TIER\", tierW), pad(\"ID\", idW), pad(\"KIND\", kindW), pad(\"STATUS\", statusW), \"TITLE\")\n\tfor _, r := range rows {\n\t\tit := r.snap\n\t\ttitle := it.Title\n\t\tif it.Deleted {\n\t\t\ttitle += \"  (deleted)\"\n\t\t}\n\t\tif len(it.Labels) \u003e 0 {\n\t\t\ttitle += \"  [\" + strings.Join(it.Labels, \", \") + \"]\"\n\t\t}\n\t\tif it.Merged {\n\t\t\ttitle += \"  ◆ merged\"\n\t\t}\n\t\tif r.count \u003e 1 {\n\t\t\ttitle += fmt.Sprintf(\"  (×%d)\", r.count)\n\t\t}\n\t\tfmt.Fprintf(w, \"%s  %s  %s  %s  %s\\n\",\n\t\t\ttierCell(it.Tier, tierW, color),\n\t\t\tpad(ShortID(it.ID), idW),\n\t\t\tpad(it.Kind, kindW),\n\t\t\tpad(it.Status, statusW),\n\t\t\ttitle)\n\t}\n\tnoun := \"entries\"\n\tif len(rows) == 1 {\n\t\tnoun = \"entry\"\n\t}\n\tfmt.Fprintf(w, \"\\n%d %s\\n\", len(rows), noun)\n}\n\n// listRows applies the clean-view transforms. With showAll, every item is its\n// own row. Otherwise superseded entries drop out and entries sharing a\n// normalized title collapse to one row (representative = most recently updated,\n// tie-broken by id) carrying the group count.\nfunc listRows(items []*entry.Snapshot, showAll bool) []listRow {\n\tif showAll {\n\t\trows := make([]listRow, 0, len(items))\n\t\tfor _, it := range items {\n\t\t\trows = append(rows, listRow{snap: it, count: 1})\n\t\t}\n\t\treturn rows\n\t}\n\tgroups := map[string][]*entry.Snapshot{}\n\tvar order []string\n\tfor _, it := range items {\n\t\tif it.Status == \"superseded\" {\n\t\t\tcontinue\n\t\t}\n\t\tkey := entry.NormalizeTitle(it.Title)\n\t\tif _, ok := groups[key]; !ok {\n\t\t\torder = append(order, key)\n\t\t}\n\t\tgroups[key] = append(groups[key], it)\n\t}\n\trows := make([]listRow, 0, len(order))\n\tfor _, key := range order {\n\t\tg := groups[key]\n\t\trep := g[0]\n\t\tfor _, it := range g[1:] {\n\t\t\tif it.UpdatedAt.After(rep.UpdatedAt) ||\n\t\t\t\t(it.UpdatedAt.Equal(rep.UpdatedAt) \u0026\u0026 it.ID.String() \u003c rep.ID.String()) {\n\t\t\t\trep = it\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t}\n\t\trows = append(rows, listRow{snap: rep, count: len(g)})\n\t}\n\treturn rows\n}\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 5: Run render tests to verify they pass**\n\nRun: `GOTOOLCHAIN=auto go test ./internal/render/...`\nExpected: PASS (both new specs and the arity-updated old ones).\n\n- [ ] **Step 6: Wire the `--all` flag into `newListCmd`**\n\nIn `cmd/kref/commands.go`, in `newListCmd`:\n\n1. Add `var all bool` next to `var includeDeleted bool` (~line 296).\n2. Change the `ListFilter` `IncludeDelete` value to `includeDeleted || all` (~line 314).\n3. Change the render closure (~line 326) to pass `all`:\n\n```go\n\t\t\t\tfunc(w io.Writer, color bool) { render.List(w, items, color, all) },\n```\n\n4. Register the flag after the `include-deleted` flag (~line 335):\n\n```go\n\tc.Flags().BoolVar(\u0026all, \"all\", false, \"show everything: superseded + tombstoned, uncollapsed\")\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 7: Write the failing CLI tests**\n\nAppend to `cmd/kref/cli_test.go` (inside the existing `Describe(\"kref CLI\", ...)`):\n\n```go\n\tIt(\"collapses duplicate-title entries in the human list and reveals them with --all\", func() {\n\t\tdir := gitRepo()\n\t\trun(\"--dir\", dir, \"init\", \"--name\", \"T\", \"--email\", \"t@e.com\")\n\t\trun(\"--dir\", dir, \"add\", \"--kind\", \"note\", \"--title\", \"Auth Design\", \"--body\", \"one\")\n\t\trun(\"--dir\", dir, \"add\", \"--kind\", \"note\", \"--title\", \"Auth Design\", \"--body\", \"two\")\n\n\t\tdef := run(\"--dir\", dir, \"list\")\n\t\tExpect(def).To(ContainSubstring(\"(×2)\"))\n\t\tExpect(def).To(ContainSubstring(\"1 entry\"))\n\n\t\tall := run(\"--dir\", dir, \"list\", \"--all\")\n\t\tExpect(all).To(ContainSubstring(\"2 entries\"))\n\t\tExpect(all).NotTo(ContainSubstring(\"(×2)\"))\n\t})\n\n\tIt(\"hides superseded entries by default but --json still returns them\", func() {\n\t\tdir := gitRepo()\n\t\trun(\"--dir\", dir, \"init\", \"--name\", \"T\", \"--email\", \"t@e.com\")\n\t\tout := run(\"--dir\", dir, \"add\", \"--kind\", \"note\", \"--title\", \"Old\", \"--body\", \"b\", \"--json\")\n\t\tvar added struct {\n\t\t\tID string `json:\"id\"`\n\t\t}\n\t\tExpect(json.Unmarshal([]byte(out), \u0026added)).To(Succeed())\n\t\trun(\"--dir\", dir, \"status\", added.ID, \"superseded\")\n\n\t\tExpect(run(\"--dir\",